ed forms that their work has gone largely unnoticed by leading members and critics in experimental poetry circles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAesthetics in literature. 0aAmerican poetryxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aCultural fusion in literature. 0aPoetics. 0aWomen and literaturezUnited States. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066615140uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081356466140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813564661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813564661/original  a978-3-11-066615-1  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK